Comment:
Pierwsza część Martwego Basenu okazała się strzałem w dziesiątkę. Film nie tylko przy relatywnie niskim budżecie zarobił mnóstwo pieniędzy, nie tylko udowodnił, że filmy z kategorią R również mogą zapełniać sale kinowe, ale pokazał wpatrzonym w MCU fanom filmów superbohaterskich jakie możliwości daje w pełni wykorzystanie potencjału komiksowych konwencji. Title: Deadpool 2 | The Trailer
Comment:
Am I the only one who didn't like the first Deadpool movie that much? I know it was a big milestone getting an R rated superhero movie, but that isn't really a necessity when you have a character who can reference the censors. The bar was set low on accuracy to so I guess most people didn't notice or didn't care about the mistakes to his character. Like him being a mutate, not a mutant. They totally ditched that connection to Wolverine. They also removed a lot of his moral ambiguity. Brutally killing your opponents can make you an antihero, but Deadpool is a straight up mercenary and is a flat-out villain sometimes. (I know he was a villain in X-Men Origins: Wolverine, but we don't talk about that movie) They made his wounds taking too slowly, having him regrow his hand to baby size in hours, as opposed to the minutes it should've taken to grow to regular size. Then while his teleportation belt and magic satchel are not necessary to include, they are some of the most entertaining parts of the character and it's a same we couldn't see them.
That's why I'm personally glad a studio that has respect for the source material is getting control of Deadpool.
